CAPE TOWN - President Cyril Ramaphosa on Tuesday announced a restriction on alcohol over the Easter period, but left a raft of other restrictions in place as the country heads into the long weekend. Ramaphosa said the country will remain on level 1, with a few changes. Unchanged restrictions include curfew from midnight until 4am. Beaches will remain open, funerals remain restricted to the maximum of 100 and interprovincial travel remains open.   Here are all the new restrictions for the Easter weekend: Gatherings   Curfew and liquor Transport and travelling Ramaphosa urged South Africans to adhere to the Easter restrictions and also reiterated that large gatherings have the potential to spread the virus, despite the application of measures around social distancing and sanitising. rudolph.nkgadima@africannewsagency.com Quiz Maker - powered by Riddle